An Act to support police recruitment and retention.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 Chapter 6, Section 116 of the general laws is hereby amended by adding the following
2 new section:-
3 Section 116K. The municipal police training committee shall, not less than annually,
4 assess the workforce status of policing in the commonwealth, with regard to its adequacy,
5 diversity, and equity, and shall make recommendations for actions necessary for the recruitment
6 and retention of law enforcement officers to meet these goals. The results of said assessment,
7 together with such recommendations, shall be filed with the executive office of public safety and
8 homeland security, the joint committee on public safety and homeland security, the House and
9 Senate Committees on Ways and Means, and the clerks of the House and Senate, whom shall
10 post them electronically for public inspection, not later than December 31.
